{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
Origin 1250-1300, ({{etyl|enm}} ''[[daierie]]'' and other forms), from {{term|dey||dairymaid}} + {{term|-ery}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈdɛəɹi/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/'dæɻɪ/}}
* {{rhymes|ɛəri}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|dair|ies}}

# A place, often on a [[farm]], where [[milk]] is processed and turned into products such as [[butter]] and [[cheese]].
# A shop selling dairy products.
# (also ''dairy products'' or ''dairy produce'') Products produced from [[milk]].
# {{NZ}} A [[corner-store]], [[superette]] or '[[mini-mart]]' of some description.

